Achievements.Achievements_BALEFUL_HARVEST_Description: Reach the 15th wave of a pumpkin moon, where evil lurks among the autumn harvest.
Achievements.Achievements_BEGONE_EVIL_Description: Smash a demon or crimson altar with a powerful, holy hammer.
Achievements.Achievements_BEHIND_THE_MASK_Description: Slay the Insane Cultist, a mad magician with powerful spells.
Achievements.Achievements_BIG_BOOTY_Description: Unlock one of the dungeon's large, mysterious chests with a special key.
Achievements.Achievements_BLOODBATH_Description: Survive a blood moon, a nocturnal event where the rivers run red and monsters swarm aplenty.
Achievements.Achievements_BONED_Description: Defeat Skeletron, the cursed guardian of the dungeon.
Achievements.Achievements_BUCKETS_OF_BOLTS_Descriptio: Defeat the three nocturnal mechanical menaces: the Twins, the Destroyer, and Skeletron Prime.
Achievements.Achievements_DAVY_JONES_LOCKER_Descripti: Defeat the Flying Dutchman, the sails of the plunderin' skies.
Achievements.Achievements_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_SLAY_A_SNOWM: Triumph over the frost legion, a festive family of maniacal snowman mobsters.

Achievements.Achievements_DRAX_ATTAX_Description: Craft a drax or pickaxe axe using hallowed bars, and the souls of the three mechanical bosses.
Achievements.Achievements_DUNGEON_HEIST_Description: Steal a key from dungeon's undead denizens, and unlock one of their precious golden chests.
Achievements.Achievements_DYE_HARD_Description: Equip a dye in every possible dye slot.
Achievements.Achievements_EXTRA_SHINY_Description: Mine a powerful ore that has been newly blessed upon your world.
Achievements.Achievements_EYE_ON_YOU_Description: Defeat the Eye of Cthulhu, an ocular menace who only appears at night.
Achievements.Achievements_FASHION_STATEMENT_Descripti: Equip armor or vanity clothing in all three social slots.
Achievements.Achievements_FAST_AND_FISHIOUS_Descripti: Complete your 50th quest for the angler.
Achievements.Achievements_FISH_OUT_OF_WATER_Descripti: Defeat Duke Fishron, mutant terror of the sea.
Achievements.Achievements_FREQUENT_FLYER_Description: Spend over 1 gold being treated by the nurse.
Achievements.Achievements_FUNKYTOWN_Description: Build or encounter a glowing mushroom field above the surface.
Achievements.Achievements_GELATIN_WORLD_TOUR_Descript: Defeat every type of slime there is!
Achievements.Achievements_GET_A_LIFE_Description: Consume a life fruit, which grows in the thick of subterranean jungle grass.
Achievements.Achievements_GOBLIN_PUNTER_Description: Triumph over a goblin invasion, a ragtag regiment of crude, barbaric, pointy-eared warriors and their shadowflame sorcerers.
Achievements.Achievements_GOOD_LITTLE_SLAVE_Descripti: Complete your 10th quest for the angler.
Achievements.Achievements_HEART_BREAKER_Description: Discover and smash your first heart crystal underground.
Achievements.Achievements_HEAVY_METAL_Description: Obtain an anvil made from iron or lead.
Achievements.Achievements_HEX_EDUCATION_Description: Defeat a Goblin Summoner, conjurers of the darkest flames.
Achievements.Achievements_I_AM_LOOT_Description: Discover a golden chest underground and take a peek at its contents.
Achievements.Achievements_ICE_SCREAM_Description: Reach the 15th wave of a frost moon, where the festive season quickly degrades into madness.
Achievements.Achievements_INDEPENDENCE_DAY_Descriptio: Defeat a Mothership, overminds of the martian invaders.
Achievements.Achievements_INTO_ORBIT_Description: You can only go down from here!
Achievements.Achievements_IT_CAN_TALK_Description: Build a house in a mushroom biome and have Truffle move in.
Achievements.Achievements_ITS_GETTING_HOT_IN_HERE_Des: Spelunk deep enough to reach the molten underworld.
Achievements.Achievements_ITS_HARD_Description: Unleash the ancient spirits of light and darkness across your world, enabling much stronger foes and showering the world with dazzling treasures (and rainbows!).
Achievements.Achievements_JEEPERS_CREEPERS_Descriptio: Stumble into a spider cavern in the underground.
Achievements.Achievements_KILL_THE_SUN_Description: Survive a solar eclipse, a day darker than night filled with creatures of horror.
Achievements.Achievements_LIHZAHRDIAN_IDOL_Descriptio: Defeat Golem, the stone-faced ritualistic idol of the lihzahrd tribe.
Achievements.Achievements_LUCKY_BREAK_Description: Survive a long fall with just a sliver of health remaining.
Achievements.Achievements_MARATHON_MEDALIST_Descripti: Travel a total of 26.2 miles on foot.
Achievements.Achievements_MASTERMIND_Description: Defeat the Brain of Cthulhu, an enormous demon brain which haunts the creeping crimson.
Achievements.Achievements_MATCHING_ATTIRE_Description: Equip armor in all three armor slots: head, chest, and feet.
Achievements.Achievements_MECHA_MAYHEM_Description: Do battle against the Twins, the Destroyer, and Skeletron Prime simultaneously and emerge victorious.
Achievements.Achievements_MINER_FOR_FIRE_Description: Craft a molten pickaxe using the hottest of materials.
Achievements.Achievements_NO_HOBO_Description: Build a house suitable enough for your first town NPC, such as the guide, to move into.
Achievements.Achievements_NOT_THE_BEES_Description: Fire a Bee Gun while wearing a full set of Bee Armor.
Achievements.Achievements_OBSESSIVE_DEVOTION_Descript: Defeat the Ancient Cultist, fanatical leader of the dungeon coven.
Achievements.Achievements_OBTAIN_HAMMER_Description: Obtain your first hammer via crafting or otherwise.
Achievements.Achievements_OOO_SHINY_Description: Mine your first nugget of ore with a pickaxe.
Achievements.Achievements_PHOTOSYNTHESIS_Description: Mine chlorophyte, an organic ore found deep among the thickest of flora.
Achievements.Achievements_PUMPKIN_SMASHER_Description: Defeat the Pumpking, the spooky lord of hallow's eve.
Achievements.Achievements_RAINBOWS_AND_UNICORNS_Descr: Fire a rainbow gun while riding on a unicorn.
Achievements.Achievements_REAL_ESTATE_AGENT_Descripti: Have all possible town NPCs living in your world.
Achievements.Achievements_ROBBING_THE_GRAVE_Descripti: Obtain a rare treasure from a difficult monster in the dungeon.
Achievements.Achievements_SERVANT_IN_TRAINING_Descrip: Complete your 1st quest for the angler.
Achievements.Achievements_SLIPPERY_SHINOBI_Descriptio: Defeat King Slime, the lord of all things slimy.
Achievements.Achievements_SMASHING_POPPET_Description: Using explosives or your trusty hammer, smash a Shadow Orb or Crimson Heart in the evil parts of your world.
Achievements.Achievements_STAR_DESTROYER_Description: Defeat the four celestial towers of the moon.
Achievements.Achievements_STAR_POWER_Description: Craft a mana crystal out of fallen stars, and consume it.
Achievements.Achievements_STICKY_SITUATION_Descriptio: Survive the slime rain, where gelatinous organisms fall from the sky in droves.
Achievements.Achievements_STILL_HUNGRY_Description: Defeat the Wall of Flesh, the master and core of the world who arises after a great, burning sacrifice.
Achievements.Achievements_STING_OPERATION_Description: Defeat the Queen Bee, the matriarch of the jungle hives.
Achievements.Achievements_SUPREME_HELPER_MINION_Descr: Complete a grand total of 200 quests for the angler.
Achievements.Achievements_SWORD_OF_THE_HERO_Descripti: Obtain a Terra Blade, forged from the finest blades of light and darkness.
Achievements.Achievements_TEMPLE_RAIDER_Description: Breach the impenetrable walls of the jungle temple.
Achievements.Achievements_THE_GREAT_SOUTHERN_PLANTKIL: Defeat Plantera, the overgrown monstrosity of the jungle's depths.
Achievements.Achievements_THERE_ARE_SOME_WHO_CALL_HIM: There are Some Who Call Him...
Achievements.Achievements_TIN_FOIL_HATTER_Description: Triumph over a martian invasion, when beings from out of this world come to scramble your brains and probe you in uncomfortable places.
Achievements.Achievements_TOPPED_OFF_Description: Attain maximum health and mana possible without accessories or buffs.
Achievements.Achievements_TROUT_MONKEY_Description: Complete your 25th quest for the angler.
Achievements.Achievements_VEHICULAR_MANSLAUGHTER_Desc: Defeat an enemy by running it over with a minecart.
Achievements.Achievements_WALK_THE_PLANK_Description: Triumph over a pirate invasion, a group of pillagers from the sea out for your booty... and your life!
Achievements.Achievements_WATCH_YOUR_STEP_Description: Become a victim to a nasty underground trap.
Achievements.Achievements_WHERES_MY_HONEY_Description: Discover a large bee's hive deep in the jungle.
Achievements.Achievements_WINTERHEARTED_Description: Defeat the Ice Queen, wicked witch of the coldest nights.
Achievements.Achievements_WORM_FODDER_Description: Defeat the Eater of Worlds, a massive worm whom dwells in the corruption.
Achievements.Achievements_YOU_CAN_DO_IT_Description: Survive your character's first full night.

Angler.Angler_Complete_0: I don't have anything for you to do right now.
Angler.Angler_Complete_1: You have entertained me enough for today, go.
Angler.Angler_Complete_2: You are done, the grand {Angler} dismisses you!
Angler.Angler_Complete_3: Only one fish a day, please go away!
Angler.Angler_Complete_4: I haven't even used the last fish you gave me.  I don't need another.
Angler.Angler_Finish_0: Oh! Thanks for the fish I asked for, now scram!
Angler.Angler_Finish_1: Awesome catch! It's all going according to plan! He he he!
Angler.Angler_Finish_2: You make a great errand monkey! Now go away!
Angler.Angler_Finish_3: Muahahahahaha! You did it! You're still in one piece though, how boring!
Angler.Angler_Finish_4: Woah!? You actually did what I asked, and survived! Nice, hand it over and beat it!
Angler.Angler_FishText_2450:
Na na na na na na na Bat-FISH! That means go digging underground, fetch it, and bring it to me!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2451:
The subterranean jungles of {WorldName} have the weirdest things! Like, there's this fish I saw that looked just like a giant bumblebee! I'm allergic to bees, so you have to catch it for me! I bet it'd taste like a tuna and honey sandwich!

(Caught in Honey)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2452:
I finally found a jungle cat that likes water! I think it's because it's also part fish. I don't know why this happened, and I don't want to know. I just want it in my hands, and make it snappy!

(Caught in Jungle Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2453:
There's a rumor going around that there are islands that float high up in the sky, and that they have amazing treasure! Who cares about that though, what's even cooler is that sometimes lakes form in the clouds, and in those lakes are fish made out of clouds! I wanna know what it tastes like, so you better go catch it for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2454:
There's a cursed fish swimming in the waters of the deepest corruption! It was forged of the cursed flames that spread from the fallen horrors that lurk down there. They say not even water can put out this fire, and that it can burn forever. I can think of some awesome things I can do with a fish like that! You gonna go get it for me, or are you too chicken!?

(Caught in Corruption)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2455:
I was reeling in the big one when this funny talking zombie burst out of the forest lake and started rambling on about this 'ferocious' species of fish made out of dirt! He says it could suffocate ten blokes his size, or something like that... I want it! NOW!

(Caught in Surface, Underground, & Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2456:
The demolitionist was raising cane about losing a stick of dynamite in the lake out in the forest. He has like, so many, so why does one matter? Apparently, because it grew fins and started swimming away! I don't know where he gets his materials to make those things, but that one is clearly possessed! Reel it in and bring it to me, I always wanted a suicide bombing fish! Don't ask why...

(Caught in Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2457:
I bet you're not brave enough to find the Eater of Plankton. A corrupt fish that was mutated from a severed piece of the Eater of Worlds itself! Capture it and bring it to me, and prove to me you're not a wuss!

(Caught in Corruption)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2458:
I love collecting those bright yellow stars that fall from the sky! I love it even more when they land on someone's head. But.. but.. nothing beats a star that falls in a foresty lake and turns into a fish! That's just totally rad, and you're just rad enough to get it for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2459:
Apparently, Demon Eyes can sometimes be amphibious. They don't fly, they swim! I want to see the look on someone's face when they find it in their bathtub! They hang around the same areas. That means you reel one in for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes & Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2460:
I don't know what's worse, a bone fish or a bone fish with HANDS. This Fish-o-Tron deep in the caverns really freaks me out! I think it's possessed by the same evil spirits that possessed that old man by the dungeon! I double duck dare you to go catch it!

(Caught in Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2461:
I was trying to sleep by the hill lakeside when this fish swooped down at me. It was flying! It also had the face of a lady and had feathers! I think I screamed louder than she did! Hey you, go make her pay for scaring me like that!

(Caught in Sky Lakes & Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2462:
There's a piece of the Hunger that morphed from the Wall of Flesh into a small fish-like thing that swims around aimlessly in the underworld and it's gross and it's yucky and I want it now!

(Caught in Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2463:
Did you know deep in the crimson, some of those creatures make this gross yellow stuff? I overheard a crazy story about a pool of it having melted together into a shape of a fish and it swims around and everything! Fetch it for me, so I can stick it in someone's toilet!

(Caught in Crimson)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2464:
Oooooohhh, I'm going to be SO rich! Deep in the caverns, there is a fish made out of gemstones! Don't ask me how, I don't know, all I know is that this fish is totally awesome and you're going to catch it for me!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2465:
There's some interesting critters to be found in the deeper Hallows, I tell you! They glow this crazy purple color and it messes with my eyes! It's totally wild, so I want you to catch a fish like that for me!

(Caught in Underground Hallow)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2466:
What's white and tan and fluffy and lives in a frozen underground lake? A mutant flinxfin! I wasn't telling a joke, you know, there really is a mutated variety of Flinx that is more adapted to an aquatic lifestyle! I want it to adapt to my fishbowl, so make sure that happens!

(Caught in Underground Tundra)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2467:
It's a whale! It's a dolphin! No, it's a penguin fish! Oh, and look, it's you! You get to bring me one! You do know they only like cold water, right?

(Caught in Tundra)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2468:
There's a really really rare type of pixie that's born with so many wings that it can't actually fly! It swims with the fishes in the lakes surrounded by that blue colored grass. My fish tank needs a lamp, so I want you to catch me that pixie!

(Caught in Hallow)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2469:
I saw a fish that had eight legs! Nope! Not happening! You're fishing it for me, so it's not alive when I hold it! That's the last time I go fishing so deep in the cavern!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2470:
You ever wonder why the lakes on the surface of the snowy areas of {WorldName} never ice over? I don't. The fish, however, do! A fish made out of ice would make a great offering to the mighty and amazing {Angler}! Go, my loyal subject, and bring me this Tundra Trout with haste!

(Caught in Surface Tundra)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2471:
Unicorns and rainbows are absolutely great! They're everywhere, even in the water. No, really, I actually saw a unicorn fish in the Hallowed lake! Your job is to reel it up and let me have it as a pet!

(Caught in Hallow)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2472:
Those demons in the underworld really like voodoo dolls, but I think there's a doll out there who was blasted with way too much magic! It turned into a fish and it does stuff on its own. I dare you to go down and get me one! I'd watch out for the boiling lava, because it burns you to death and that won't get me my fish!

(Caught in Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2473:
I know something youuuuu don't! Fine, I'll tell you, there's a terrifying creature that flies among the stars! I'm not making this up! It's called a Wyvern! But, but, you knew that already, right? Well what you don't know is that they are born and raised as tadpoles! So, they're actually like.. well, a frog! Hop to it and get me one!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2474:
You won't believe it! I caught a fish in the forest at night that was already dead! Then it tried to eat me! I threw it away and ran! Now I want to stick it in someone's dresser to see what happens, so go fish it back up for me will ya?!

(Caught in Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2475:
I found this spectacular place draped in giant glowing mushrooms! Everything was blue! I was picking some of the mushrooms I found next to a glistening blue lake, when one of the mushrooms snapped at me and swam away! I want to give it a taste of its own medicine, and give it a good chompin'! What I mean is, you gotta get it for me!

(Caught in Glowing Mushroom Fields)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2476:
Did you know there's magical islands that float up high in the sky? Bet you didn't! They say angels live in the sky, and I believe those angels have fins and gills and swim around! I believe you must catch one for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2477:
Ow! Don't get near me! I got stung by a Bloody Man-O-War! In case you're not smart enough to know what that is, it's the most menacing jellyfish in all of {WorldName}! Go to that rotten crimson and catch it if you dare! 

(Caught in Crimson)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2478:
Normally I could care less if I see fishbones floating in the water underground, but this one was swimming! What, you thought that only human skeletons still flailed about in {WorldName}? Get it for me so I can stick it in someone's bed!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2479:
Out in the forest, I was fishing right? Well guess what! A bunny hopped up to me! Then another one hopped up, and another... suddenly I'm surrounded by bunnies! One even swam up to me from the water, but it had no legs! I fell outta my chair in surprise and all the bunnies scurried off! I want that bunny fish as a pet, so you better catch it for me! Pronto!

(Caught in Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2480:
Yarr matey! Shiver me timbers! Avast, scallywags! There's a pirate captain who once had a pet fish named Cap'n Tunabeard, but during a big storm the fishbowl fell overboard! It has a hook for a tail, and an eyepatch and everything! You need to fetch me that fish, so I can be as cool as a pirate! Obviously it's out in the ocean somewhere! Duh!

(Caught in Ocean)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2481:
I saw this bright orange and colorful fish by the ocean, and it was looking around frantically as though it was seeking a lost family member! Go catch it for me, so that another one will show up looking frantically for him instead!

(Caught in Ocean)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2482:
I hear in the underworld, that the King of all demons is actually a fish! Just imagine the absolute power I would have if you caught it for me!

(Caught in Caverns)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2483:
Those Derplings in the jungle are the most scary creatures I've ever seen! Good thing is, sometimes they don't have legs! These ones live in the water and are a lot less scary! Catch me one now so I can see what they taste like without being scared half to death!

(Caught in Jungle Surface)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2484:
There's a legend of a mighty being known as the Fishron! It's part pig, part dragon, and part FISH! I hear it hangs around in the frozen subterranean lakes of the coldest part of the world! I'm not going there, so YOU go catch it and makes sure it lands in my hands! I'm so excited!

(Caught in Underground Tundra)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2485:
A really long fish that looks like a sword's sheath swims in the murky waters of the corruption! It looks a lot like ebonstone, so don't let it fool you! That's right, you. You're catching it, not me!

(Caught in Corruption)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2486:
Watch your step when wading through jungle waters! Why? No, not because I care about you being eaten by piranhas. I care because you'll step on one of my favorite kinds of fish, the Mud Fish! I also care a lot that you're going to grab me one as a pet!

(Caught in Jungle)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2487:
In the forest, the slimes are kinda gross. Slimefish are even more so! I don't want to swim with slimes, so yoink one out of the water for me!

(Caught Anywhere)
Angler.Angler_FishText_2488:
Piranhas and sharks are ugly! Soooo ugly! Did you know there's a fish that looks very pretty and still can eat your face off? I would pay 2 platinum to see that happen, by the way... To the point, though, you catchy for me. Just make sure I have it before you lose your face!

(Caught Jungle Surface)

Dialog.Dialog_100: Why purify the world when you can just blow it up?
Dialog.Dialog_101: If you throw this one in the bathtub and close all the windows, it'll clear your sinuses and pop your ears!
Dialog.Dialog_103: Hey, could you sign this Griefing Waiver?
Dialog.Dialog_105: Explosives are da' bomb these days.  Buy some now!
Dialog.Dialog_106: It's a good day to die!
Dialog.Dialog_107: I wonder what happens if I... (BOOM!)... Oh, sorry, did you need that leg?
Dialog.Dialog_108: Dynamite, my own special cure-all for what ails ya.
Dialog.Dialog_109: Check out my goods; they have explosive prices!
Dialog.Dialog_10: Check out my dirt blocks; they are extra dirty.
Dialog.Dialog_110: I keep having vague memories of tying up a woman and throwing her in a dungeon.
Dialog.Dialog_111: ... we have a problem! Its a blood moon out there!
Dialog.Dialog_112: T'were I younger, I would ask {nurse} out. I used to be quite the lady killer.
Dialog.Dialog_113: That Red Hat of yours looks familiar...
Dialog.Dialog_114: Thanks again for freeing me from my curse. Felt like something jumped up and bit me.
Dialog.Dialog_115: Mama always said I would make a great tailor.
Dialog.Dialog_116: Life's like a box of clothes; you never know what you are gonna wear!
Dialog.Dialog_117: Of course embroidery is hard! If it wasn't hard, no one would do it! That's what makes it great.
Dialog.Dialog_118: I know everything they is to know about the clothierin' business.
Dialog.Dialog_119: Being cursed was lonely, so I once made a friend out of leather. I named him Wilson.
Dialog.Dialog_11: Boy, that sun is hot! I do have some perfectly ventilated armor.
Dialog.Dialog_120: Thank you for freeing me, human.  I was tied up and left here by the other goblins.  You could say that we didn't get along very well.
Dialog.Dialog_121: I can't believe they tied me up and left me here just for pointing out that they weren't going east!
Dialog.Dialog_122: Now that I'm an outcast, can I throw away the spiked balls? My pockets hurt.
Dialog.Dialog_123: Looking for a gadgets expert? I'm your goblin!
Dialog.Dialog_124: Thanks for your help. Now, I have to finish pacing around aimlessly here. I'm sure we'll meet again.
Dialog.Dialog_126: Hey...what's {mech} up to? Have you...have you talked to her, by chance?
Dialog.Dialog_127: Hey, does your hat need a motor? I think I have a motor that would fit exactly in that hat.
Dialog.Dialog_128: Yo, I heard you like rockets and running boots, so I put some rockets in your running boots.
Dialog.Dialog_129: Silence is golden. Duct tape is silver.
Dialog.Dialog_12: The sun is high, but my prices are not.
Dialog.Dialog_130: YES, gold is stronger than iron. What are they teaching these humans nowadays?
Dialog.Dialog_131: You know, that mining helmet-flipper combination was a much better idea on paper.
Dialog.Dialog_132: Goblins are surprisingly easy to anger. In fact, they could start a war over cloth!
Dialog.Dialog_133: To be honest, most goblins aren't exactly rocket scientists. Well, some are.
Dialog.Dialog_134: Do you know why we all carry around these spiked balls? Because I don't.
Dialog.Dialog_135: I just finished my newest creation! This version doesn't explode violently if you breathe on it too hard.
Dialog.Dialog_136: Goblin thieves aren't very good at their job. They can't even steal from an unlocked chest!
Dialog.Dialog_137: Thanks for saving me, friend!  This bondage was starting to chafe.
Dialog.Dialog_139: Oh, how heroic! Thank you for saving me, young lady!
Dialog.Dialog_13: Oh, great. I can hear {mech} and {nurse} arguing from here.
Dialog.Dialog_140: Oh, how heroic! Thank you for saving me, young man!
Dialog.Dialog_141: Now that we know each other, I can move in with you, right?
Dialog.Dialog_142: Well, hi there, {guide}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_143: Well, hi there, {demo}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_144: Well, hi there, {goblin}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_145: Well, hi there, {nurse}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_146: Well, hi there, {mech}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_147: Well, hi there, {dryad}! What can I do for you today?
Dialog.Dialog_148: Want me to pull a coin from behind your ear? No? Ok.
Dialog.Dialog_149: Do you want some magic candy? No? Ok.
Dialog.Dialog_14: Have you seen Chith...Shith.. Chat... The big eye?
Dialog.Dialog_150: I make a rather enchanting hot chocolate if you'd be inter...No? Ok.
Dialog.Dialog_151: Are you here for a peek at my crystal ball?
Dialog.Dialog_152: Ever wanted an enchanted ring that turns rocks into slimes? Well neither did I.
Dialog.Dialog_153: Someone once told me friendship is magic. That's ridiculous. You can't turn people into frogs with friendship.
Dialog.Dialog_154: I can see your future now... You will buy a lot of items from me!
Dialog.Dialog_155: I once tried to bring an Angel Statue to life. It didn't do anything.
Dialog.Dialog_156: Thanks!  It was just a matter of time before I ended up like the rest of the skeletons down here.
Dialog.Dialog_157: Hey, watch where you're going! I was over there a little while ago!
Dialog.Dialog_158: Hold on, I've almost got wifi going down here.
Dialog.Dialog_159: But I was almost done putting blinking lights up here!
Dialog.Dialog_15: Hey, this house is secure, right? Right? {myPlayerName}?
Dialog.Dialog_160: DON'T MOVE. I DROPPED MY CONTACT.
Dialog.Dialog_161: All I want is for the switch to make the... What?!
Dialog.Dialog_162: Oh, let me guess. Didn't buy enough wire. Idiot.
Dialog.Dialog_163: Just-could you just... Please? Ok? Ok. Ugh.
Dialog.Dialog_164: I don't appreciate the way you're looking at me. I am WORKING right now.
Dialog.Dialog_165: Hey, {myPlayerName}, did you just come from {goblin}'s? Did he say anything about me by chance?
Dialog.Dialog_166: {dealer} keeps talking about pressing my pressure plate. I told him it was for stepping on.
Dialog.Dialog_167: Always buy more wire than you need!
Dialog.Dialog_168: Did you make sure your device was plugged in?
Dialog.Dialog_169: Oh, you know what this house needs? More blinking lights.
Dialog.Dialog_16: Not even a blood moon can stop capitalism. Let's do some business.
Dialog.Dialog_170: You can tell a Blood Moon is out when the sky turns red. There is something about it that causes monsters to swarm.
Dialog.Dialog_171: Hey, buddy, do you know where any deathweed is? Oh, no reason; just wondering, is all.
Dialog.Dialog_172: If you were to look up, you'd see that the moon is red right now.
Dialog.Dialog_173: You should stay indoors at night. It is very dangerous to be wandering around in the dark.
Dialog.Dialog_174: Greetings, {myPlayerName}. Is there something I can help you with?
Dialog.Dialog_175: I am here to give you advice on what to do next.  It is recommended that you talk with me anytime you get stuck.
Dialog.Dialog_176: They say there is a person who will tell you how to survive in this land... oh wait. That's me.
Dialog.Dialog_178: If you want to survive, you will need to create weapons and shelter. Start by chopping down trees and gathering wood.
Dialog.Dialog_179: When you have enough wood, open your crafting menu and create a workbench. Workbenches allow you to create more complicated things, as long as you are standing close to them.
Dialog.Dialog_17: Keep your eye on the prize, buy a lense!
Dialog.Dialog_180: You can build a shelter by placing wood or other blocks in the world. Don't forget to create and place walls.
Dialog.Dialog_181: Once you have a wooden sword, you might try to gather some gel from the slimes. Combine wood and gel to make a torch!
Dialog.Dialog_182: To interact with backgrounds, use a hammer!
Dialog.Dialog_183: You should do some mining to find metal ore. You can craft very useful things with it.
Dialog.Dialog_184: Now that you have some ore, you will need to turn it into a bar in order to make items with it. This requires a furnace!
Dialog.Dialog_185: You can create a furnace out of torches, wood, and stone. Make sure you are standing near a work bench.
Dialog.Dialog_186: You will need an anvil to make most things out of metal bars.
Dialog.Dialog_187: Anvils can be crafted out of iron, or purchased from a merchant.
Dialog.Dialog_188: Underground are crystal hearts which can be used to increase your max life. You can smash them with a pickaxe.
Dialog.Dialog_189: If you gather 5 fallen stars, they can be combined to create an item that will increase your magic capacity.
Dialog.Dialog_18: Kosh, kapleck Mog. Oh sorry, that's klingon for 'Buy something or die.'
Dialog.Dialog_190: Stars fall all over the world at night. They can be used for all sorts of usefull things. If you see one, be sure to grab it because they disappear after sunrise.
Dialog.Dialog_191: There are many different ways you can attract people to move in to our town. They will of course need a home to live in.
Dialog.Dialog_192: In order for a room to be considered a home, it needs to have a door, a chair, a table, and a light source.  Make sure the house has walls as well.
Dialog.Dialog_193: Two people will not live in the same home. Also, if their home is destroyed, they will look for a new place to live.
Dialog.Dialog_194: You can use the housing interface to assign and view housing. Open your inventory and select the house icon.
Dialog.Dialog_195: If you want a merchant to move in, you will need to gather plenty of money. 50 silver coins should do the trick!
Dialog.Dialog_196: For a nurse to move in, you might want to increase your maximum life.
Dialog.Dialog_197: If you had a gun, I bet an arms dealer might show up to sell you some ammo!
Dialog.Dialog_198: You should prove yourself by defeating a strong monster. That will get the attention of a dryad.
Dialog.Dialog_199: Make sure to explore the dungeon thoroughly. There may be prisoners held deep within.
Dialog.Dialog_19: {myPlayerName} is it? I've heard good things, friend!
Dialog.Dialog_1: I hope a scrawny kid like you isn't all that is standing between us and Cthulhu's Eye.
Dialog.Dialog_200: Perhaps the old man by the dungeon would like to join us now that his curse has been lifted.
Dialog.Dialog_201: Hang on to any bombs you might find. A demolitionist may want to have a look at them.
Dialog.Dialog_202: Are goblins really so different from us that we couldn't live together peacefully?
Dialog.Dialog_203: I heard there was a powerful wizard who lives in these parts.  Make sure to keep an eye out for him next time you go underground.
Dialog.Dialog_204: If you combine lenses at a demon altar, you might be able to find a way to summon a powerful monster. You will want to wait until night before using it, though.
Dialog.Dialog_205: You can create worm bait with rotten chunks and vile powder. Make sure you are in a corrupt area before using it.
Dialog.Dialog_206: Demonic altars can usually be found in the corruption. You will need to be near them to craft some items.
Dialog.Dialog_207: You can make a grappling hook from a hook and 3 chains. Skeletons found deep underground usually carry hooks, and chains can be made from iron bars.
Dialog.Dialog_208: If you see a pot, be sure to smash it open. They contain all sorts of useful supplies.
Dialog.Dialog_209: There is treasure hidden all over the world. Some amazing things can be found deep underground!
Dialog.Dialog_20: I hear there's a secret treasure... oh never mind.
Dialog.Dialog_210: Smashing a shadow orb will sometimes cause a meteor to fall out of the sky. Shadow orbs can usually be found in the chasms around corrupt areas.
Dialog.Dialog_211: You should focus on gathering more life crystals to increase your maximum life.
Dialog.Dialog_212: Your current equipment simply won't do. You need to make better armor.
Dialog.Dialog_213: I think you are ready for your first major battle. Gather some lenses from the eyeballs at night and take them to a demon altar.
Dialog.Dialog_214: You will want to increase your life before facing your next challenge. Fifteen hearts should be enough.
Dialog.Dialog_215: The ebonstone in the corruption can be purified using some powder from a dryad, or it can be destroyed with explosives.
Dialog.Dialog_216: Your next step should be to explore the corrupt chasms.  Find and destroy any shadow orb you find.
Dialog.Dialog_217: There is a old dungeon not far from here. Now would be a good time to go check it out.
Dialog.Dialog_218: You should make an attempt to max out your available life. Try to gather twenty hearts.
Dialog.Dialog_219: There are many treasures to be discovered in the jungle, if you are willing to dig deep enough.
Dialog.Dialog_21: Angel Statue you say? I'm sorry, I'm not a junk dealer.
Dialog.Dialog_220: The underworld is made of a material called hellstone. It's perfect for making weapons and armor.
Dialog.Dialog_221: When you are ready to challenge the keeper of the underworld, you will have to make a living sacrifice. Everything you need for it can be found in the underworld.
Dialog.Dialog_222: Make sure to smash any demon altar you can find. Something good is bound to happen if you do!
Dialog.Dialog_223: Souls can sometimes be gathered from fallen creatures in places of extreme light or dark.
Dialog.Dialog_224: Ho ho ho, and a bottle of... Egg Nog!
Dialog.Dialog_225: Care to bake me some cookies?
Dialog.Dialog_226: What? You thought I wasn't real?
Dialog.Dialog_227: I managed to sew your face back on. Be more careful next time.
Dialog.Dialog_228: That's probably going to leave a scar.
Dialog.Dialog_229: All better. I don't want to see you jumping off anymore cliffs.
Dialog.Dialog_22: The last guy who was here left me some junk... er I mean... treasures!
Dialog.Dialog_230: That didn't hurt too bad, now did it?
Dialog.Dialog_231: As if living underground wasn't bad enough, jerks like you come in while I'm sleeping and steal my children.
Dialog.Dialog_232: Between you and me, {dryad} is the only one I trust. She is the only one here who hasn't tried to eat me or use me in a potion.
Dialog.Dialog_233: I tried to lick myself the other day to see what the big deal was, everything started glowing blue.
Dialog.Dialog_234: Everytime I see the color blue, it makes me depressed and lazy.
Dialog.Dialog_235: You haven't seen any pigs around here have you? My brother lost his leg to one.
Dialog.Dialog_236: Everyone in this town feels a bit off. I woke up to the clothier chewing on my foot last night.
Dialog.Dialog_237: I'll give you a discount on your wears if you can convince {truffle} to come over for a...sizing.
Dialog.Dialog_238: I feel like {truffle} is a bit misunderstood, he really is a fun guy.
Dialog.Dialog_23: I wonder if the moon is made of cheese...huh, what? Oh yes, buy something!
Dialog.Dialog_240: I don't know the 'Truffle Shuffle,' so stop asking!
Dialog.Dialog_241: There's been such a huge rumor that's being spread about me, 'If you can't beat him, eat him!'
Dialog.Dialog_242: Oy, whatchu got in you jiminy fluffer?
Dialog.Dialog_243: Should I become an air pirate? I've considered becoming an air pirate.
Dialog.Dialog_244: Be it what it would, a jetpack would suit you nicely!
Dialog.Dialog_245: I'm feeling a bit peevish as of late, so enough with your palaver you ragamuffin!
Dialog.Dialog_246: I'm mighty curious about that {cyborg} fellow. By what manner of consumption does he maintain such locomotion?
Dialog.Dialog_247: That captain fellow seems to me to be 'pretty well over the bay' if you know what I mean!
Dialog.Dialog_249: I like your... gear. Does it come in brass?
Dialog.Dialog_24: Did you say gold?  I'll take that off of ya.
Dialog.Dialog_250: Once you enter hallowed land, you will see a rainbow in the sky. I can help you with painting that if you want.
Dialog.Dialog_251: Check out {partygirl}. Now that's a girl who can paint the town red!
Dialog.Dialog_252: I know the difference between turquoise and blue-green. But I won't tell you.
Dialog.Dialog_253: I'm all out of titanium white, so don't even ask.
Dialog.Dialog_254: Try swirly pink and purple, it works, I swear!
Dialog.Dialog_255: No, no, no... There's TONS of different grays! Don't get me started...
Dialog.Dialog_256: I hope it doesn't rain again until this paint dries. That would be a disaster!
Dialog.Dialog_257: I bring you the richest colors in exchange for your riches!
Dialog.Dialog_258: My dear, what you're wearing is much too drab. You absolutely must take a lesson in dyeing your tired attire!
Dialog.Dialog_259: The only kind of wood I would bother dyeing is RICH Mahogany. Dyeing any other wood is such a waste.
Dialog.Dialog_25: You better not get blood on me.
Dialog.Dialog_260: You must do something about {pirate}.  Everytime he comes over here, it takes me a week to get the smell off!
Dialog.Dialog_261: Which doctor am I? The Witch Doctor am I.
Dialog.Dialog_262: The heart of magic is nature. The nature of hearts is magic.
Dialog.Dialog_263: {nurse} may help heal your body, but I can make you embody healing.
Dialog.Dialog_264: Choose wisely, {myPlayerName}, my commodities are volatile and my dark arts, mysterious.
Dialog.Dialog_265: We have to talk. It's... it's about parties.
Dialog.Dialog_266: I can't decide what I like more: parties, or after-parties.
Dialog.Dialog_267: We should set up a blinkroot party, and we should also set up an after-party.
Dialog.Dialog_268: Wow, {myPlayerName}, meeting an adventurous man like you makes me want to party!
Dialog.Dialog_269: Put up a disco ball and then I'll show you how to party.
Dialog.Dialog_270: I went to Sweden once, they party hard, why aren't you like that?
Dialog.Dialog_271: My name's {partygirl} but people call me party pooper. Yeah I don't know, it sounds cool though.
Dialog.Dialog_272: Do you party? Sometimes? Hm, okay then we can talk...
Dialog.Dialog_273: I'm no landlubber, but it's better to have lubbed and lost than never to have lubbed at all.
Dialog.Dialog_274: Yo ho ho and a bottle of....blinkroots!
Dialog.Dialog_275: YAR!  Funny ye should be mentionin' parrots b'cause...um...What t'were we talkin' 'bout?
Dialog.Dialog_276: {myPlayerName}, Ye be one o' the finest lookin' lassies this here captain's seen in many a fortnight!
Dialog.Dialog_277: Stay off me booty, ya scallywag!
Dialog.Dialog_278: What in blazes are ye talkin' about? Moby Dick is mine!
Dialog.Dialog_27: If you're going to die, do it outside.
Dialog.Dialog_280: And then Unit 492-8 said, 'Who do you think I am, Unit 472-6?' HA. HA. HA.
Dialog.Dialog_281: My expedition efficiency was critically reduced when a projectile impacted my locomotive actuator.
Dialog.Dialog_282: This sentence is false , or is it?
Dialog.Dialog_283: So that 'punk' lookin' chick is an inventor, eh? I think I could show her a thing or two!
Dialog.Dialog_284: Sure, me and {pirate} are pals, but I hate it when his parrot does his business on me. That stuff's corrosive!
Dialog.Dialog_285: I built myself a taste mechanism, so I can drink some ale!
Dialog.Dialog_286: Sometimes I come off a bit... Get it? a bit?
Dialog.Dialog_287: Short back and sides' is it?
Dialog.Dialog_288: Those highlights really bring out your eyes!
Dialog.Dialog_289: My hands are sticky from all that... wax.
Dialog.Dialog_28: What is that supposed to mean?!
Dialog.Dialog_290: Tea? Coffee? Or is it just orange juice again?
Dialog.Dialog_291: Doll, we seriously need to fix those split ends.
Dialog.Dialog_292: Gurrllll! You are my favorite gossip ever.
Dialog.Dialog_293: Which aftershave can I interest you in today, sir?
Dialog.Dialog_294: Sit down for a second and I'll have you steppin' razor.
Dialog.Dialog_295: Either you have style, or you get styled.
Dialog.Dialog_296: For you I think we'll do something... low maintenance.
Dialog.Dialog_297: I tried using one of the Dye Master's products once. Ends fried. Disaster.
Dialog.Dialog_298: Oh you poor, poor thing. Just... just sit down here. It'll be okay. Shhhh.
Dialog.Dialog_29: I don't think I like your tone.
Dialog.Dialog_2: Look at that shoddy armor you're wearing. Better buy some more healing potions.
Dialog.Dialog_300: Hello sir, I'm {Stylist}, and I'll be your barber today.
Dialog.Dialog_301: Just a little off the top?  That's no fun...
Dialog.Dialog_302: I hope you like what I did to {PartyGirl}'s hair!
Dialog.Dialog_303: There is nothing I can do for {Demolitionist}'s singed head. He's a lost cause.
Dialog.Dialog_304: Tipping IS optional, but remember I have access to scissors and your head.
Dialog.Dialog_305: This is a cut-throat razor by the way.
Dialog.Dialog_306: You better stay outta my hair tonight, hun. I just sharpened my scissors, and I'm looking for an excuse to use them!
Dialog.Dialog_307: Mhmm, I heard from {PartyGirl} that {Mechanic}'s friend {Nurse} spent her boyfriend's last paycheck on shoes.
Dialog.Dialog_308: One time I put a wig on {Cyborg} just so I could cut his hair. I think he kinda liked it!
Dialog.Dialog_309: I tried to visit {Stylist} one time. She just looked at me and said 'nope.'
Dialog.Dialog_30: Why are you even here? If you aren't bleeding, you don't need to be here. Get out.
Dialog.Dialog_310: I think it is about time I got my hair did!
Dialog.Dialog_311: Did you even try to brush your hair today?
Dialog.Dialog_312: So a pixie cut, would you like to keep some lady burns?
Dialog.Dialog_313: I have no problem cleaning up ears and eyebrows, but I draw the line at nose hair.
Dialog.Dialog_314: Alright, you sit and marinate. I'll be back to rinse your color out in 25 minutes...
Dialog.Dialog_315: Thanks hun! Now I can finally do my hair.
Dialog.Dialog_316: I would have given you a free cut if you'd come earlier.
Dialog.Dialog_317: "Don't go exploring with scissors", they said. "You won't get trapped in a spider's web", they said!
Dialog.Dialog_318: Ew, my hair, there's spider web all over it!
Dialog.Dialog_319: Meet me behind {Guide}'s house in about three hours, I think I have something you will find very appealing.
Dialog.Dialog_320: That {Merchant}, he really has no appreciation for a really good deal.
Dialog.Dialog_321: I sell only what I can get. {Clothier} keeps hounding me for exotic clothing.
Dialog.Dialog_322: Hmm, you look like you could use an Angel Statue! They slice, and dice, and make everything nice!
Dialog.Dialog_323: I don't refund for "buyer's remorse..." Or for any other reason, really.
Dialog.Dialog_324: Buy now and get free shipping!
Dialog.Dialog_325: I sell wares from places that might not even exist!
Dialog.Dialog_326: You want two penny farthings!? Make it one and we have a deal.
Dialog.Dialog_327: Combination hookah and coffee maker! Also makes julienne fries!
Dialog.Dialog_328: Come and have a look! One pound fish! Very, very good! One pound fish!
Dialog.Dialog_329: If you're looking for junk, you've come to the wrong place.
Dialog.Dialog_32: Have you seen that old man pacing around the dungeon? He looks troubled.
Dialog.Dialog_330: A thrift shop?  No, I am only selling the highest quality items on the market.
Dialog.Dialog_331: Smashing a crimson heart will sometimes cause a meteor to fall out of the sky. Crimson hearts can usually be found in the chasms around crimtane areas.
Dialog.Dialog_332: Have you tried using purification powder on the crimstone of the crimson?
Dialog.Dialog_333: You must cleanse the world of this crimson.
Dialog.Dialog_334: Psst! I might have a job for you. Don't think you can say no, either!
Dialog.Dialog_335: I want a fish and you're going to find me one! Ask me about it!
Dialog.Dialog_336: Hey! Just the sacrifi- I mean competent fishing master that I've been looking for!
Dialog.Dialog_337: {Angler} wants YOU as the official {WorldName} errand monkey!
Dialog.Dialog_338: Whaaaat?! Can't you see I'm winding up fishing line??
Dialog.Dialog_339: I have enough fish! I don't need your help right now!
Dialog.Dialog_33: I wish {Demolitionist} would be more careful.  I'm getting tired of having to sew his limbs back on every day.
Dialog.Dialog_340: There's no chefs in all of {WorldName}, so I have to cook all this fish myself!
Dialog.Dialog_341: Hey! Watch it! I'm setting up traps for my biggest prank ever! No one will see it coming! Don't you dare tell anyone!
Dialog.Dialog_342: Let a kid give you some advice, never touch your tongue to an ice block! Wait, forget what I said, I totally want to see you do it!
Dialog.Dialog_343: Ever heard of a barking fish?! I haven't, I'm just wondering if you did!
Dialog.Dialog_344: {WorldName} is filled to the brim with the most outlandish kinds of fish!
Dialog.Dialog_345: I'm bummed out! There's probably been fish that have gone extinct before I even was born, and that's not fair!
Dialog.Dialog_346: I don't have a mommy or a daddy, but I have a lot of fish! It's close enough!
Dialog.Dialog_347: Heh heh, you shoulda seen the look on {Dryad}'s face when I stuck that piranha tooth in the chair!
Dialog.Dialog_348: I have a request for you! No, I don't care that there's a zombie apocalypse right now!
Dialog.Dialog_349: Hurry up and listen! I need you to catch something for me right now!
Dialog.Dialog_34: Hey, has {dealer} mentioned needing to go to the doctor for any reason? Just wondering.
Dialog.Dialog_350: I hate blood moons! I stay up all night because of all the scary noises!
Dialog.Dialog_351: Blood moon is the worst time to fish! The fish bite, yes, but so do the zombies!
Dialog.Dialog_352: There's a bajillion monsters running around out there right now!
Dialog.Dialog_353: Thanks, I guess, for saving me or whatever. You'd be a great helper minion!
Dialog.Dialog_354: Wha? Who might you be? I totally wasn't just drowning or anything!
Dialog.Dialog_355: You saved me! You're awful nice, I could use you... er, I mean, totally hire you to do some awesome stuff for me!
Dialog.Dialog_356: Got any spare bones for sale? I'm looking to replace my broken hip... again.
Dialog.Dialog_357: Excellent! Someone's finally come by to take some of these maggots off my hands.
Dialog.Dialog_358: There's no illness or condition that can't be cured by some of my Slime Oil! Trust me, it works, just look at my lively figure!
Dialog.Dialog_359: You've got a real backbone coming way down here, how 'bout ya buy somethin?
Dialog.Dialog_35: I need to have a serious talk with {Guide}. How many times a week can you come in with severe lava burns?
Dialog.Dialog_360: You would not believe some of the things people throw at me... Wanna buy some of it?
Dialog.Dialog_361: I'd lend you a hand, but last time I did that, I didn't get it back for a month
Dialog.Dialog_362: Stay away from the spiders. They'll suck out your insides and leave you a hollow shell of a man. Trust me on this one.
Dialog.Dialog_363: The only things constant in this world are death and taxes, I've got both!
Dialog.Dialog_364: You again? Suppose you want more money!?
Dialog.Dialog_365: Must everyone open and shut doors so incredibly noisily around here?!
Dialog.Dialog_366: I see you're free of time, as usual. Can't imagine what work life would be for your kind of folk.
Dialog.Dialog_367: Yes, yes, yes! -- I'll give you your share in just a moment. I'd think you to be a bit more patient, what with me doing all the work and all.
Dialog.Dialog_368: What does a man have to do to be left alone in this place? Go bugger someone less busy!
Dialog.Dialog_369: ...two barrels of molasses, plus -- Oh, nevermind that, you're here. Here's your money.
Dialog.Dialog_36: I think you look better this way.
Dialog.Dialog_370: Just between you and me... I have no idea why they're bothering to pay the rent
Dialog.Dialog_371: Tried to get {Dryad} to pay me with favors once, now I have fungus growing in strange places.
Dialog.Dialog_372: Go tell {ArmsDealer} to stop offering to pay me with ammo, I don't even own a gun.
Dialog.Dialog_373: Why don't YOU try collecting money from {Demolitionist} and not lose a hand or foot or...
Dialog.Dialog_374: I just came from {Merchant}'s. He wanted to know if I took credit cards.
Dialog.Dialog_37: Eww... What happened to your face?
Dialog.Dialog_380: Here's your cut of the taxes that I've taken from our surplus population!
Dialog.Dialog_381: Here you are again, taking all my coin! Just grab it and begone from my sight!
Dialog.Dialog_382: Bah! Here, take your shillings and get out of my sight!
Dialog.Dialog_383: This is all you're gonna get for now, not a penny more! Take it and spend it wisely.
Dialog.Dialog_38: MY GOODNESS! I'm good, but I'm not THAT good.
Dialog.Dialog_390: ...And people call me greedy? No, I have nothing else for you.
Dialog.Dialog_391: Oh, so you just see me as a coin sign, eh? 'Cus every time you see me, you ask me.
Dialog.Dialog_392: Don't you ever stop just to say 'Hi?'
Dialog.Dialog_393: Bah! You again? You just grabbed some of my coin just moments ago, so bugger off and come back later!
Dialog.Dialog_394: I just gave you half a crown five minutes ago! Scram!
Dialog.Dialog_395: Reaching into my moneybags again already!? And you call ME greedy.
Dialog.Dialog_396: You just received your pay, and not a farthing more! Get out!
Dialog.Dialog_397: Money doesn't grow on trees, so don't overpick my fruit! Bah!
Dialog.Dialog_398: You already managed to spend every pence I paid you!? Bah, I'm not a charity, go kill a slime!
Dialog.Dialog_399: Not so fast! You got your money, now begone!
Dialog.Dialog_39: Dear friends we are gathered here today to bid farewell... Oh, you'll be fine.
Dialog.Dialog_3: I feel like an evil presence is watching me.
Dialog.Dialog_400: Begging so soon?! Don't look at me like I'll have a change of heart overnight!
Dialog.Dialog_401: Make sure to smash any crimson altar you can find. Something good is bound to happen if you do!
Dialog.Dialog_402: Crimson altars can usually be found in the crimson. You will need to be near them to craft some items.
Dialog.Dialog_403: You can create a bloody spine with vertebrae. Make sure you are in a crimtane area before using it.
Dialog.Dialog_40: You left your arm over there. Let me get that for you...
Dialog.Dialog_41: Quit being such a baby! I've seen worse.
Dialog.Dialog_44: Hold on, I've got some cartoon bandages around here somewhere.
Dialog.Dialog_45: Walk it off, {PlayerName}, you'll be fine. Sheesh.
Dialog.Dialog_46: Does it hurt when you do that? Don't do that.
Dialog.Dialog_47: You look half digested. Have you been chasing slimes again?
Dialog.Dialog_49: That's not the biggest I've ever seen... Yes, I've seen bigger wounds for sure.
Dialog.Dialog_4: Sword beats paper! Get one today.
Dialog.Dialog_52: I'm sorry, but you can't afford me.
Dialog.Dialog_53: I'm gonna need more gold than that.
Dialog.Dialog_54: I don't work for free you know.
Dialog.Dialog_56: I can't do anymore for you without plastic surgery.
Dialog.Dialog_58: I heard there is a doll that looks very similar to {guide} somewhere in the underworld.  I'd like to put a few rounds in it.
Dialog.Dialog_59: Make it quick! I've got a date with {nurse} in an hour.
Dialog.Dialog_5: You want apples? You want carrots? You want pineapples? We got torches.
Dialog.Dialog_60: I want what {nurse} is sellin'. What do you mean, she doesn't sell anything?
Dialog.Dialog_61: {dryad} is a looker.  Too bad she's such a prude.
Dialog.Dialog_62: Don't bother with {demo}, I've got all you need right here.
Dialog.Dialog_63: What's {demo}'s problem? Does he even realize we sell completely different stuff?
Dialog.Dialog_64: Man, it's a good night not to talk to anybody, don't you think, {myPlayerName}?
Dialog.Dialog_65: I love nights like tonight.  There is never a shortage of things to kill!
Dialog.Dialog_66: I see you're eyeballin' the Minishark.. You really don't want to know how it was made.
Dialog.Dialog_67: Hey, this ain't a movie, pal. Ammo is extra.
Dialog.Dialog_68: Keep your hands off my gun, buddy!
Dialog.Dialog_69: Have you tried using purification powder on the ebonstone of the corruption?
Dialog.Dialog_6: Lovely morning, wouldn't you say? Was there something you needed?
Dialog.Dialog_70: I wish {dealer} would stop flirting with me. Doesn't he realize I'm 500 years old?
Dialog.Dialog_71: Why does {merchant} keep trying to sell me an angel statues? Everyone knows that they don't do anything.
Dialog.Dialog_72: Have you seen the old man walking around the dungeon? He doesn't look well at all...
Dialog.Dialog_73: I sell what I want! If you don't like it, too bad.
Dialog.Dialog_74: Why do you have to be so confrontational during a time like this?
Dialog.Dialog_75: I don't want you to buy my stuff. I want you to want to buy my stuff, ok?
Dialog.Dialog_76: Dude, is it just me or is there like a million zombies out tonight?
Dialog.Dialog_77: You must cleanse the world of this corruption.
Dialog.Dialog_79: The sands of time are flowing. And well, you are not aging very gracefully.
Dialog.Dialog_7: Night will be upon us soon, friend. Make your choices while you can.
Dialog.Dialog_80: What's this about me having more 'bark' than bite?
Dialog.Dialog_81: So two goblins walk into a bar, and one says to the other, 'Want to get a Goblet of beer?!
Dialog.Dialog_82: I cannot let you enter until you free me of my curse.
Dialog.Dialog_83: Come back at night if you wish to enter.
Dialog.Dialog_84: My master cannot be summoned under the light of day.
Dialog.Dialog_85: You are far too weak to defeat my curse.  Come back when you aren't so worthless.
Dialog.Dialog_86: You pathetic fool.  You cannot hope to face my master as you are now.
Dialog.Dialog_87: I hope you have like six friends standing around behind you.
Dialog.Dialog_88: Please, no, stranger. You'll only get yourself killed.
Dialog.Dialog_89: You just might be strong enough to free me from my curse...
Dialog.Dialog_8: You have no idea how much Dirt Blocks sell for overseas.
Dialog.Dialog_90: Stranger, do you possess the strength to defeat my master?
Dialog.Dialog_91: Please! Battle my captor and free me! I beg you!
Dialog.Dialog_92: Defeat my master, and I will grant you passage into the Dungeon.
Dialog.Dialog_93: Trying to get past that ebonrock, eh?  Why not introduce it to one of these explosives!
Dialog.Dialog_94: Hey, have you seen a clown around?
Dialog.Dialog_95: There was a bomb sitting right here, and now I can't seem to find it...
Dialog.Dialog_96: I've got something for them zombies alright!
Dialog.Dialog_98: Would you rather have a bullet hole or a grenade hole? That's what I thought.
Dialog.Dialog_99: I'm sure {nurse} will help if you accidentally lose a limb to these.
Dialog.Dialog_9: Ah, they will tell tales of {myPlayerName} some day... good ones I'm sure.
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeAccepted_0: Brilliant, my dear! You have brought me an exquisite sample of the world's beautiful colors and aroma. In exchange, you may take this special bottle of dye.
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeAccepted_1: You bring me a beautiful, rare flower... yes, yes? Take this bottle of special dye for your troubles, friend!
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeAccepted_2: Fantabulous, wonderful friend! With this delicate specimen, I may mix the most amazing dyes {WorldName} has ever seen! You may take this one right away!
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeRejected_0: Oh no no, this will not do.  For these money is no good, you must return to me with a rare specimen of a plant!
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeRejected_1: You think you can pull a fast one on {DyeTrader}, I don't think so! I only take the rarest of flowers for these special bottles!
Dialog.Dialog_DyeTradeRejected_2: These dye bottles? Sorry dear friend, these don't take coin. I only take the most precious and rare of flora in exchange for one of this!
Dialog.Dialog_177: You can use your pickaxe to dig through dirt, and your axe to chop down trees. Just place your cursor over the tile and press the Use Item button!

LoadingTip.LoadingTip_0: You can change your spawn point by placing and using a _OpenItemMarkup_bed_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_10: There are _OpenEmphasisMarkup_floating islands_CloseMarkup_ in the sky.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_11: Sometimes you can find NPCs hidden around the World.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_12: During a _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Blood Moon_CloseMarkup_, zombies can open doors.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_13: You can continuously use some items by holding down _UseOrAttack_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_15: _OpenItemMarkup_Torches_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_glowsticks_CloseMarkup_ can be a light for you in dark places, when all other lights go out. Torches won't work underwater, but glowsticks will.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_16: Don't fall into lava without an _OpenItemMarkup_Obsidian Skin Potion_CloseMarkup_!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_17: You won't take falling damage if you have a _OpenItemMarkup_Lucky Horseshoe_CloseMarkup_. Look for them on floating islands.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_18: Walking on Hellstone and Meteorite can burn you! Protect yourself by equipping an _OpenItemMarkup_Obsidian Skull_CloseMarkup_ or similar accessory.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_19: _OpenItemMarkup_Life Crystals_CloseMarkup_ are hidden around the World. Use them to increase your health.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_1: If you find a _OpenItemMarkup_Magic Mirror_CloseMarkup_, you can use it to teleport back to your spawn point.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_20: Some ores require better pickaxes to mine.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_21: Bosses are easier to defeat with friends.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_22: Press _SmartCursor_ to switch between Cursor Modes.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_23: Bows and guns require the proper _OpenItemMarkup_ammo_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_24: You can press _Action1_ to send unwanted items to the Trash.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_25: When speaking to a vendor, you can sell items in your Inventory by pressing _Action1_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_26: The _OpenNpcMarkup_Old Man_CloseMarkup_ at the Dungeon is a _OpenNpcMarkup_Clothier_CloseMarkup_, if only someone could lift his _OpenEmphasisMarkup_curse_CloseMarkup_...
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_27: Merchants love money. If you save up enough, one might move in!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_28: Hold onto an explosive to attract a _OpenNpcMarkup_Demolitionist_CloseMarkup_ to your house.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_29: Make sure you have empty, valid rooms to attract new inhabitants.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_2: _OpenItemMarkup_Torches_CloseMarkup_ require _OpenItemMarkup_wood_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_gels_CloseMarkup_ to craft. Gels can be obtained by defeating slimes.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_30: Slay a boss to attract a _OpenNpcMarkup_Dryad_CloseMarkup_ to your house. She can tell you the state of _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Corruption_CloseMarkup_, _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Crimson_CloseMarkup_, and _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Hallow_CloseMarkup_ in your World.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_31: Advanced players may wish to remap their buttons. You can do this from the Controls Menu in Settings (Pause Menu during gameplay).
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_32: Wear a _OpenItemMarkup_Mining Helmet_CloseMarkup_ if you don't want to use torches.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_34: You can remove torches with _Cancel_ or with a Pickaxe.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_35: Other players can loot your chests! If you don't trust them, use a _OpenItemMarkup_safe_CloseMarkup_ or _OpenItemMarkup_piggy bank_CloseMarkup_; those items have storage that is exclusive to each player.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_36: Defeat the boss in The Underworld to change the World forever. Find a _OpenItemMarkup_Guide Voodoo Doll_CloseMarkup_ and hurl it into the infernal lava to summon him.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_37: _OpenItemMarkup_Demon Altars_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_Crimson Altars_CloseMarkup_ can't be destroyed with a normal hammer. You have to pwn them.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_3: When exploring, it helps to keep some platforms on hand. They can be crafted from numerous materials, such as wood, glass, or even bones.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_41: A _OpenItemMarkup_pet_CloseMarkup_ can be your best friend.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_42: If you dig deep enough, you'll end up in _OpenEmphasisMarkup_The Underworld_CloseMarkup_!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_43: _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Santa Claus_CloseMarkup_ is real. He comes to town after the _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Frost Legion_CloseMarkup_ is defeated (and 'tis the season).
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_44: Don't shake a _OpenItemMarkup_snow globe_CloseMarkup_ unless you want to summon the _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Frost Legion_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_45: In your Inventory, you can press _UseOrAttack_ to equip items such as armor or accessories directly to a usable slot.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_46: You can use _OpenItemMarkup_Hallowed Seeds_CloseMarkup_, _OpenItemMarkup_Holy Water_CloseMarkup_, or _OpenItemMarkup_Pearlstone_CloseMarkup_ to make Hallowed ground.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_47: The Hallow is the only place where Corruption and Crimson cannot spread.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_48: The Corruption is full of chasms. Mind the gaps.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_4: _OpenItemMarkup_Falling Stars_CloseMarkup_ sometimes appear at night. Collect 3 of them to craft a  _OpenItemMarkup_Mana Crystal_CloseMarkup_ you can use to increase your _OpenItemMarkup_mana_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_51: The _OpenItemMarkup_Cloud in a Bottle_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_Shiny Red Balloon_CloseMarkup_ accessories both improve your ability to jump. Combine them to make a _OpenItemMarkup_Cloud in a Balloon_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_52: If you store your coins in a chest or piggy bank, you will be less likely to lose them.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_53: To craft potions, place a _OpenItemMarkup_bottle_CloseMarkup_ on a _OpenItemMarkup_table_CloseMarkup_ to make an _OpenItemMarkup_alchemy station_CloseMarkup_, or find an _OpenItemMarkup_Alchemy Table_CloseMarkup_ in the Dungeon. Double, double, toil and trouble!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_54: If your house doesn't have background walls, monsters will be able to spawn inside.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_55: Wearing armor made out of all the same material gives you an extra bonus.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_56: Build a _OpenItemMarkup_furnace_CloseMarkup_ to craft metal bars out of ore.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_57: You can harvest _OpenItemMarkup_cobwebs_CloseMarkup_ and turn them into _OpenItemMarkup_silk_CloseMarkup_. You can use silk to craft beds, sofas, and more!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_58: You can buy _OpenItemMarkup_wires_CloseMarkup_ from a Mechanic and use them to create traps, pumping systems, or other elaborate devices.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_59: You can plant _OpenItemMarkup_acorns_CloseMarkup_ to grow new trees.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_5: If you're sick of getting knocked around, try equipping a _OpenItemMarkup_Cobalt Shield_CloseMarkup_. You can find one in the Dungeon.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_60: _OpenItemMarkup_Grappling hooks_CloseMarkup_ are invaluable tools for exploration. Try crafting them with hooks or gems.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_61: A room in a house can have wood platforms as a floor or ceiling, but NPCs need at least one solid block to stand on.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_62: You can destroy _OpenItemMarkup_Shadow Orbs_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_Crimson Hearts_CloseMarkup_ with a hammer or explosives, but prepare yourself for the forces they unleash.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_63: When dealing with a _OpenEmphasisMarkup_Goblin Army_CloseMarkup_, crowd control is key.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_64: The best wizard people use _OpenItemMarkup_Mana Flowers_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_65: Use _OpenEmphasisMarkup_suspicious looking_CloseMarkup_ items at your own risk!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_67: The _OpenNpcMarkup_Goblin Tinkerer_CloseMarkup_ found in underground caverns will sell you many useful items, including a _OpenItemMarkup_Tinkerer's Workshop_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_68: The _OpenMenuMarkup_Housing_CloseMarkup_ section of the Equipment Menu allows you to decide what rooms you want your NPCs to live in.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_69: _OpenItemMarkup_Seeds_CloseMarkup_ can be used to grow a variety of useful ingredients for crafting potions.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_6: Some projectiles such as _OpenItemMarkup_arrows_CloseMarkup_ and _OpenItemMarkup_shurikens_CloseMarkup_ can be gathered and reused after firing them.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_70: You can check if a room is _OpenEmphasisMarkup_valid_CloseMarkup_ housing from the _OpenMenuMarkup_Housing_CloseMarkup_ section of the Inventory Menu.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_71: If you get lost or need to find another player, open the _OpenMenuMarkup_World Map_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_72: Fishing is a fantastic source of crafting ingredients, accessories, and loot crates!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_73: Nothing improves your mobility like Wings. Who wouldn't want to fly?
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_74: Riding minecarts is one of the best ways of getting around. You can build your own tracks, or find them underground.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_75: Life Crystals not enough for you? Eventually, Life Fruit will grow in the Jungle, and can give you an extra boost to your health.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_76: Info accessories don't need to be equipped to provide you and nearby friends with useful information; you can just leave them in your inventory.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_77: Change your clothes in game at a Dresser or talk to the Stylist for a new hairdo.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_78: Mounts grant the player increased mobility and unique abilities. Each one is unique!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_79: Looking for a challenge? Try Expert mode!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_7: If you need to remove background walls, craft a _OpenItemMarkup_hammer_CloseMarkup_.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_80: Be careful around Martian Probes. If they scan you, they'll summon a Martian Invasion!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_81: When a Solar Eclipse happens, tons of strange and creepy monsters show up.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_82: A Pumpkin Medallion can be used to summon the Pumpkin Moon. Spooky!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_83: Feeling up for the chill of winter? Use a Naughty Present to summon the Frost Moon!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_84: The Arms Dealer knows more about guns than anyone. If you find one, he might move in.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_85: The Mechanic got lost in the Dungeon. You'll have to help her out if you want her to move in.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_86: Once you use a Life Crystal, a Nurse might move in! Speak to her for healing at any time . . . for a price, of course.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_87: If you ever want to get stylish, try dyes! The Dye Trader can help you turn some ingredients into new dye colors.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_88: If you need a new haircut, go check out a nearby spider biome. Stylists always end up lost in them!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_89: Regular wood and stone not vibrant enough for you? A Painter will move in and sell paints if enough townsfolk move in.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_8: Rope can really help you get around while exploring caves. You can even craft it into a coil of rope which can be thrown and automatically unfolds!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_90: Its worth it to explore your Oceans. You can find treasure, dyes, and even sleeping fishermen.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_91: You could get a Witch Doctor to come to your world if you defeat the Queen Bee.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_92: The Party Girl won't move in unless your world is full of other townsfolk. Afterall, what's a party without lots of guests.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_93: The Wizard sells some useful magic artifacts, but he has a tendency to wander off underground.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_94: The Tax Collector spends his days wandering the Underworld as a Tortured Soul. If only there were a way to purify him . . .
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_95: Mushroom biomes can be grown above ground as well as below. Friendly Truffles will sometimes make themselves at home in surface mushroom biomes.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_96: Pirates are so unpredictable. First they invade your world, and then they move into your houses!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_97: If you ever defeat any giant robots, a Steampunker might move in to your world.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_98: If you like rockets, the Cyborg may have some for sale.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_99: The Traveling Merchant never stays in one place for long, but he always bring different wares when he visits!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_9: Got some extra walls or platforms? You can turn them back into their original ingredients!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_100: Not all Skeletons are evil. Some even sell things!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_101: Many statues have mysterious properties. Try wiring them to switches or pressure plates.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_102: Medusas in Marble Caves can turn their enemies to stone. If you get caught in midair, the fall can be brutal.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_103: A few rare armors have a special ability that can be activated by double-tapping Down on the left stick.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_104: The last place where you died is marked on your map by a red X. Head back quickly to recover your lost coins or gear!
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_105: With a chest open, use Restock to automatically refill your ammo, potions, and any other stackable items that you're already carrying in inventory.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_106: In Expert mode, enemies are tougher and many aspects of the world become more challenging. However, many rare and powerful items are only available in this mode.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_107: Before fighting a boss, it's a good idea to prepare an arena with health regenerating devices and room to maneuver. A builder's instinct is as valuable as a powerful swordarm.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_108: Sand can be crafted into glass, which is used to make bottles and many other useful items.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_109: Honey is renowned for its regenerative properties.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_110: Now when you open a chest, you can start crafting using the items in the chest along with the ones in your inventory.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_111: The Equipment Menu is here! Finally your Grappling Hooks, Minecarts, Pets and Mounts have a home.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_112: Favorited items stay in your inventory unless you manually move them; they can't be accidentally thrown or deposited with the Quick Stack function.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_113: Going fishing? Dawn and dusk are the best times to try for something good.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_114: A _OpenItemMarkup_Sextant_CloseMarkup_ displays the Moon's current phase. Many things in the world pay attention to the Moon.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_115: The humble Sunflower is rumored to hold a spark of purity.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_116: Some walls and platforms can be deconstructed into their component materials.
LoadingTip.LoadingTip_117: Curious about how something works? Visit the official Terraria wiki and the official Terraria forums to learn all kinds of useful things!

Tutorial.Tutorial_BuildCursor: Placing items and structures is easier in the Manual Cursor Mode. Press _SmartCursor_ to switch your Cursor Mode.
Tutorial.Tutorial_BuildHouse:
To start, build walls and a ceiling. Give yourself plenty of room inside. If you don't have enough wood (or stone), gather more.

A shelter must be at least 6 blocks high and 10 blocks wide.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Chest: If you activate a chest or vendor NPC, a separate section will appear for it.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Congratulations: Congratulations, you have completed the tutorial. There are only a few areas to explore on this floating island. When you are ready, exit the tutorial and create yourself a whole new World!
Tutorial.Tutorial_CoverWall: Make sure to cover the entire background.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftCategories: There are several categories of crafting items. You can switch between them by pressing _ToggleLeft_ and _ToggleRight_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftDoor_ExtraInfo: If you don't have enough wood, chop down more trees.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftDoor: Stand near your crafting table and craft a door.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftingInfo: When you are standing near a work bench or other crafting station (such as an anvil or furnace), more recipes will be available to build in your Crafting menu.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Crafting: Press _HotbarDecrement_ or _HotbarIncrement_ until you switch to the Crafting section.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftTorch: The gel and wood you collected can be crafted into a torch. Select the torch icon and press _Confirm_ to create it.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftWall_ExtraInfo: If you don't have enough wood, chop down more trees.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftWall: Craft a bunch of wood walls at your work bench.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftWorkbench_ExtraInfo: If you don't have enough wood, chop down more trees.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftWorkbench: To craft a door, you need a work bench. Craft a work bench and place it inside your house.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Cursor: Press (or hold) _UseOrAttack_ to perform actions with the current item. Aim with _RightStick_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_DoorHole:
You'll need a door to get in and out. Remove 3 blocks from the bottom of a wall to make room.

Use a pickaxe to remove blocks.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Drop: To permanently delete an item, move it to the Trash slot.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Equipment: Press _TabRight_ to switch to the Equip section.
Tutorial.Tutorial_EquipScreen: The Equip section is where you place armor and accessories. Items in Vanity slots appear on your character, but do not give armor bonuses.
Tutorial.Tutorial_FallDown: You can fall through wood platforms by tilting down _LeftStick_. Try falling through the platform.
Tutorial.Tutorial_GuideInfo: The Guide is the first NPC who can move into your house. You can talk to him for tips or details about crafting ingredients.
Tutorial.Tutorial_HammerInfo: If you ever want to destroy background walls, you can craft a hammer to do so.
Tutorial.Tutorial_HotBar: At the top of your screen is the Inventory Bar. You can switch between items with _HotbarDecrement_ & _HotbarIncrement_. Now switch to your sword.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Intro: Terraria is a game about adventuring to the ends of the World and defeating villainous bosses along the way. This tutorial will teach you the basics.
Tutorial.Tutorial_InventoryExplanation: The Inventory Menu is split into sections. This area is your main Inventory. The top row of item slots is your Inventory Bar. There are also slots for ammo (such as arrows) or coins.
Tutorial.Tutorial_InventoryOpen: All the items you pick up go into your Inventory. Press _Inventory_ to open the Inventory Menu.
Tutorial.Tutorial_LivableInfo: This room is now livable for NPCs. As you progress, there are many NPCs who can move into your house if you have enough livable rooms for them.
Tutorial.Tutorial_MinedOre: As you dig deeper underground, you will find better ores. Some may require a better pickaxe to mine.
Tutorial.Tutorial_MonsterInfo: Terraria is full of monsters, especially at night. Luckily there are many weapons you can find to help you.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Movement: Use _LeftStick_ to move between slots. Press _Confirm_ to pick up and place stacks of items. Press _InventorySlotAction1_ to move one item at a time.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Night: It's dangerous to be outside at night. Build a shelter before it gets dark.
Tutorial.Tutorial_PlaceChair: Craft a chair and place it in your house.
Tutorial.Tutorial_PlaceDoor: Now place the door in the space in the wall. This can be tricky, and is easiest in the Manual Cursor Mode, _SmartCursor_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_PlaceTorch: Now place a torch on the walls or floor of your house. This is easiest in Manual Cursor Mode, _SmartCursor_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_PlaceWall: Panel the background of your house with wood walls. This is easiest in the Auto Cursor Mode, _SmartCursor_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Placing_ExtraInfo: Build enough so you can jump out of the hole.
Tutorial.Tutorial_PlacingCursor: Remember you can switch between Cursor Modes at any time by pressing _SmartCursor_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Placing: In Manual Cursor Mode _RightStick_ acts like a mouse. Aim the cursor and press _UseOrAttack_ to place wood platforms.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Potions: If you get hurt, you will heal over time. You can also use food or healing potions.
Tutorial.Tutorial_SafetyInfo: Your house is now safe. For a room to be livable for NPCs, it needs: a table (such as your work bench), a chair, and a light source (such as a torch).
Tutorial.Tutorial_SelectAxe: To chop down a tree you must use an axe. Switch to your axe.
Tutorial.Tutorial_SelectPick: To create better items and explore the vast underground, you will need to dig down and mine ore with a pickaxe. Switch to your pickaxe.
Tutorial.Tutorial_SelectPlatform: Now select the wood platforms in your Inventory Bar.
Tutorial.Tutorial_SwordAttack: An evil monster has appeared. Defeat it with your sword by pressing _UseOrAttack_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_Torch: Killing that slime gave you a gel. If you had wood to combine it with, you could craft a torch. Let's gather some wood.
Tutorial.Tutorial_UseAxe: Chop down a tree by aiming toward one and holding _UseOrAttack_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_UseDoor: You can open or close your door. Aim at it and press _OpenOrActivate_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_UsePick: Nearby there is a vein of ore. Mine it all by aiming toward it and holding _UseOrAttack_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_WallInfo: You're almost done. To make your house safe, you will need to panel the background of your house with walls (such as wood walls).
Tutorial.Tutorial_WoodPlatform:
If you get stuck in a hole, you can place wood platforms to get out. Craft 6 wood platforms.

Press _Inventory_ to open the Inventory Menu. Switch to Crafting with _TabLeft_.
Tutorial.Tutorial_CraftScreen: If you want to find out more about a recipe's ingredients, you can press _NavigateRight_ to look at the Ingredients.
